transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: Hello.

Speaker 1: Hello, how are we doing, sir?

Speaker 2: Yes, I was calling, checking on my order.

Speaker 1: I got the tracking number and stuff like that.

Speaker 2: I'm just not all that good with that type of stuff.

Speaker 1: Oh, let me check for you.

Speaker 2: Mm-hmm.

Speaker 1: Let me check.

Speaker 2: He said that one of them was delivered – some stuff was delivered yesterday.

Speaker 1: Did you check?

Speaker 2: I never – yeah, I checked.

Speaker 1: I looked outside my door.

Speaker 2: I never received it.

Speaker 1: It's in the mailbox.

Speaker 2: It's in the mailbox?

Speaker 1: Yes, USPS mailbox.

Speaker 2: Oh, okay.

Speaker 1: I checked the mailbox earlier and got something that was for, I think, yesterday –

Speaker 2: I mean, the day before yesterday, but maybe I didn't get the mail for yesterday.

Speaker 1: If you want, we can stay on the phone if you're not far from me.

Speaker 2: No, I'm at work.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: And there wasn't enough to check on.

Speaker 2: And you say – how many orders was it?

Speaker 1: So you had the Viagra 10 tablet, and you have one bottle of testosterone booster.

Speaker 2: We usually go with the Viagra.

Speaker 1: Mm-hmm.

Speaker 2: Oh, I didn't order that, though.

Speaker 1: I just ordered the Viagra.

Speaker 2: I didn't order the booster.

Speaker 1: Oh, that's your order for booster, here.

Speaker 2: One bottle.

Speaker 1: Someone else – oh, man.

Speaker 2: How much was that?

Speaker 1: $29.95.

Speaker 2: No, I didn't want that.

Speaker 1: I wanted the Viagra.

Speaker 2: I wanted – well, how can I get – can I send that back?

Speaker 1: Because I don't want that.

Speaker 2: Yeah, you can write refuse return on it, then, the testosterone bottle.

Speaker 1: I can write what on it?

Speaker 2: Refuse return on the testosterone bottle.

Speaker 1: But don't get confused.

Speaker 2: Make sure that you return the right one because you have two packages.

Speaker 1: So don't return the wrong one.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so why would I need the booster if I got the Viagra?

Speaker 2: I don't know.

Speaker 1: That's how the order came.

Speaker 2: Maybe you accidentally placed it.

Speaker 1: I'm not sure.

Speaker 2: Maybe.

Speaker 1: We're just receiving orders, and then we fulfill whatever comes in the system, though.

Speaker 2: Oh, maybe that's what happened.

Speaker 1: Okay, so when I get it back, when I get it and I want to return it,

Speaker 2: so what I have to do to return it?

Speaker 1: Write refuse return on the package.

Speaker 2: That's all.

Speaker 1: Refuse return and put it back in the mailbox?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Usually patient order that, but maybe you did it by accident.

Speaker 2: I don't know.

Speaker 1: I think I did.

Speaker 2: Yeah, you know, ED, it goes with testosterone as well, but it's like an engine.

Speaker 1: You've got to look at the different components.

Speaker 2: But people just look in one direction.

Speaker 1: They forget about their prostate.

Speaker 2: They forget about their blood flow.

Speaker 1: You know what I'm saying?

Speaker 2: You've got to fix the whole engine to get your Ferrari going, basically.

Speaker 1: You know what I'm saying?

Speaker 2: So that's the thing.

Speaker 1: And both of them was 10 tablets.

Speaker 2: Yes, it was 10 tablets.

Speaker 1: Okay, I'll see when I receive it.

Speaker 2: When I get home today, I'll check.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay, good.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Thank you, sir.

Speaker 1: You're all set.

Speaker 2: Yep.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Appreciate you.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
